comment.body:
@deividas-pelakauskas Thanks for the feature request.
Collections with WebSocket and gRPC requests have limited functionality for now. We are tracking this internally.

Can you also share your workflow with the exported collection JSON?

@unreleased I understand your use case and that's why we have the "Encode URL automatically" setting which you can turn off to disable automatic-encoding.

![Screenshot 2022-08-24 at 5 36 30 PM](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/4865836/186414918-c0db5187-7a7a-4e72-bc70-2f20bdb9d172.png)

This works for characters in `[33, 255]` range but anything outside it must be encoded due to a [hard check](https://github.com/nodejs/node/blob/v18.7.0/lib/_http_client.js#L170..L174) in Node.js.

@moshest We've added support for decoding additional error details in Postman v9.29.

Currently, we support [error_details.proto](https://github.com/googleapis/googleapis/blob/master/google/rpc/error_details.proto) types. Everything else is represented in binary form.

![Screenshot 2022-08-19 at 4 25 12 PM](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/4865836/185603853-41cf3fd2-2e61-4d17-9f1a-34b93c35ddba.png)

@b4brijesh You can now configure "Maximum response message size" under gRPC request settings.
There’s no limit on the request/outgoing message size.

![Screenshot 2022-08-19 at 4 09 01 PM](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/4865836/185601396-6c32ad1b-df0e-45f7-aa98-34f8302ef92d.png)

issue.body:
This fixes support for proto files that have nested messages or enums declared within groups, like this:

```proto
syntax = "proto2";

message Foo {
  repeated group Field = 1 {
    message Bar {
      optional bool my_bool = 2;
    }

    optional string my_string = 3;
    optional Bar my_bar = 4;
  }
}

```

